hops.name: Akoya
hops.genetic_origin: Zenith x Hopsteiner male
hops.brewhouse: Perle, Aurora, Hallertauer Tradition, Northern Brewer

hops.name: Alora
hops.genetic_origin: Hopsteiner Breeding Program
hops.aroma_spec: Peach, yuzu fruit, sweet melon, apricot
hops.description: Unique chemistry - Over 50% of total oils are Selinene with high bound 3MH thiols (5X the amount of Cascade).

hops.name: Bravo
hops.genetic_origin: Zeus x (98004 x USDA 19058m).
hops.description:
Bravo is tried and true in the kettle, offering a polished and pleasant bitterness profile. Candied lime and sweet fruit notes emerge when used as a late hop or dry hop addition. Bravo is "the bittering hop of choice" among many brewers.

Hop Highlights:
14—17% Alpha
3—5% Beta
High Geraniol
Pleasant Bitterness

hops.name: Helios
hops.description: Variety specs may change over different crop years

hops.name: HS16660
hops.aroma_spec: Tropical fruit, berry, fruit candies, citrus
hops.description: High intensity aroma variety with high 4MMP free thiol and geraniol composition.

hops.name: Altus
hops.genetic_origin: 50 % Apollo, 25 % Wye Target

hops.name: Calypso
hops.genetic_origin: A diploid aroma-type hop, originated from a cross between Hopsteiner breeding female 98005 and a Hopsteiner male derived from Nugget and USDA 19058m.
hops.description:
Calypso is a unique variety, delivering aromas "unlike anything else." Exploding with tropical fruit and sweet apple-pear, try dry hopping your next beer with Calypso!

Hop Highlights:
12—14% Alpha
5—6% Beta
Unique Aroma
Early Maturing Variety

hops.name: Apollo
hops.genetic_origin: Zeus x (98001 x USDA 19058m).
hops.description:
Apollo packs punch. Traditionally a high-alpha bittering variety, Apollo also lends grapefruit citrus and resinous notes when applied as a dry-hop. "Think West Coast–style IPA’s and you know exactly what this hop delivers." Try substituting Apollo for Zeus or Nugget in your next brew.

Hop Highlights:
15—19% Alpha
5.5—8% Beta
High Yield
Excellent Storage Stability

hops.name: Contessa
hops.genetic_origin: A cross out of Fuggle and a Cascade male

hops.name: Delta
hops.genetic_origin: A diploid aroma-type hop, originated from a cross between Fuggle and a male derived from Cascade.
hops.description:
Originally bred as a Willamette replacement, Delta’s superior yield give it an edge. Spicy and earthy with slight citrus aromas, Delta has been labeled a "Super Willamette." It’s a great variety substitute for Willamette or Fuggle.

Hop Highlights:
5.5—7% Alpha
5.5—7% Beta

hops.name: Eureka!
hops.genetic_origin: Apollo, Merkur
hops.aroma_spec: black currant, dark fruits, strong herbal notes, pine tree
hops.description:
Complex in nature, Eureka is dank and resinous with fruity notes ranging all the way from tropical-citrus to dark stone fruit. Eureka rounds out blends and truly shines as a late hop addition. A variety for the "classic hop head," Eureka is one you won’t want to miss!

Hop Highlights:
17—19% Alpha
4.5—6% Beta
High Total Oil
Plays well with others

hops.name: Lemondrop
hops.genetic_origin: Aroma-type hop, originated from a cross between Cascade and USDA 19058 male
hops.description:
The name truly says it all. Lemondrop offers a "unique lemon-citrus character with a pleasant aroma." The bright citrus and subtle herbaceous notes are perfect for sessionable beers. While ales tend to bring out her sweeter side, Lemondrop is delicate and refined enough for quality lagers.

Hop Highlights:
5—7% Alpha
4—6% Beta

hops.name: Lotus
hops.genetic_origin: 50% Eastern Gold, 25% Apollo, Cascade, USDA 19058

hops.name: Solero
hops.genetic_origin: Cascade x Hopsteiner male

hops.name: Sultana
hops.genetic_origin: 50 % Nugget, 25 % Zeus, 25 % USDA 19058m
hops.description:
Sultana is BIG. A monster of a plant with gigantic cones, she has a high total oil content to boot! With pineapple, pine and bright citrus notes, Sultana is sure to make "one hell of an IPA!" 

Hop Highlights:
13—15% Alpha
4—5% Beta
High Total Oil
High Yield

hops.name: Trident
hops.genetic_origin: Trident™ is comprised of three unique Pacific Northwest-grown hop varieties
hops.dry_hopping: Hazy IPA, American Pale Ale, IPA, Lager
hops.description: Trident™ is a specialized blend with a much wider range of aroma and flavor characteristics than any single hop variety could generate on its own. Although, Trident™ is suitably balanced as is, it could also be added with others to build an even more unique and potent flavor profile.

hops.name: Zeus
hops.genetic_origin: A super high alpha variety developed in the Yakima valley as part of the Hopsteiner breeding program.

hops.name: HS09326
hops.genetic_origin: 75% Cascade
hops.aroma_spec: berry jam, tropical fruit, grapefruit, herbal

hops.name: Amarillo ®
hops.genetic_origin: Unknown
hops.description: AMARILLO® is a trademark owned by Virgil Gamache Farms, Inc.

hops.name: Aramis
hops.genetic_origin: Aramis is the product of a 2002 cross between the French variety Strisselspalt and the English variety WGV (Whitbread Golding Variety).
hops.aroma_spec: Sweet, spicy notes, with hints of citrus and herbs

hops.name: Ariana
hops.genetic_origin: Herkules x wild hop male
hops.aroma_spec: black berries, blackcurrant, peach, pear, tropical fruits, resinous

hops.name: Bitter Gold
hops.genetic_origin: The lineage goes back to Brewer's Gold, Bullion, Comet and Fuggle and was released in 1999

hops.name: Brewers Gold
hops.genetic_origin: A open pollinated cross of a Manitoban wild hop (BB1) originating in England.

hops.name: Cascade
hops.genetic_origin: Open pollinated of a Fuggle seedling, itself derived from crosses between Fuggle and the Russian hop Serebrianka.

hops.name: Cashmere
hops.genetic_origin: Cashmere was released by Washington State University in 2013 and resulted out of Cascade and Northern Brewer

hops.name: Centennial
hops.genetic_origin: Selected from a cross between a Brewers Gold and Fuggle seedling and a selected USDA male with largely Brewers Gold parentage.

hops.name: Callista
hops.genetic_origin: Hallertauer Tradition x Hüll male breeding line
hops.aroma_spec: Pleasant hoppy note, intensively fruity, apricot, passion fruit, red berries

hops.name: Chinook
hops.genetic_origin: From a cross between Petham Golding and a USDA-selected male with high alpha-acids and good storage properties.

hops.name: Cluster
hops.genetic_origin: Not known but possibly the result of a cross between an English variety and an American male hop.

hops.name: Columbus / Tomahawk
hops.genetic_origin: Tomahawk is a bittering hop of recent origin.

hops.name: Comet
hops.genetic_origin: Comet was originally released as a high alpha by the USDA in 1974. Its parentage is English Sunshine and a native American hop giving it a “wild American” characteristic.

hops.name: Crystal
hops.genetic_origin: A triploid Hallertau Mittelfrueh x (Cascade x USDA 65009-64034M). Half-sister of Mt. Hood, Liberty and Ultra.

hops.name: Diamant
hops.genetic_origin: Released in 2019 originating from Spalter and a male derived at the Hüll breeding institute

hops.name: El Dorado
hops.genetic_origin: The lineage goes back to Brewer's Gold, Bullion, Comet and Fuggle and was released in 1999
hops.aroma_spec: Tropical mango, pear, stone fruit, and candied lemon

hops.name: Fuggle
hops.genetic_origin: Seedling selected in 1875 in England.

hops.name: Galena
hops.genetic_origin: Open pollinated seedling of Brewers Gold.

hops.name: Glacier
hops.genetic_origin: Cross between Elsasser F and 8685-014 M. Genetic composition is 1/2 Elsasser 5/32 Brewer's Gold, 1/8 Northern Brewer, 1/16 Bullion, 1/32 Early Green, 1/32 German Aroma hop, 1/64 East Kent Golding, 1/128 Bavarian and 9/128 unknown.

hops.name: Golding (UK)
hops.genetic_origin: An old, long established English variety originating in Kent; the name Goldings covers a group of similar varieties variously known as Cobbs, Amos, Early Bird, Eastwell, Bramling, Canterbury and Mathon.

hops.name: Riwaka
hops.genetic_origin: Released in 1997 by New Zealand's Plant & Food Hop Research Centre
hops.description: An intense fruit forward hop that delivers breathtaking citrus characteristics

hops.name: Hallertau Blanc
hops.genetic_origin: Cascade x Huell male

hops.name: Hallertauer Magnum
hops.genetic_origin: A Galena cross (751513M) originating in Germany, released in 1993.

hops.name: Hallertauer Merkur
hops.genetic_origin: A cross between Hallertauer Magnum and 81/8/13, bred in Huell.

hops.name: Hallertauer Mittelfrueh
hops.genetic_origin: A landrace variety originating in Germany.

hops.name: Hallertauer Taurus
hops.genetic_origin: A German high alpha cross between 82/39/37 and 85/54/15M, bred in Huell; released in 1995.

hops.name: Hallertauer Tradition
hops.genetic_origin: A cross between Hallertauer Gold and 75/15/106M originating in Germany, released in 1993.

hops.name: Herkules
hops.genetic_origin: A German high alpha cross variety, bred in Huell.
hops.brewhouse: Hallertauer Taurus, Hallertauer Magnum, Hallertauer Merkur

hops.name: Hersbrucker
hops.genetic_origin: A landrace variety originating Germany.

hops.name: Huell Melon
hops.genetic_origin: Cascade x Huell male

hops.name: Horizon
hops.genetic_origin: Released in 1998 from a cross between a selected high alpha-acid and high beta-acid USDA female and a selected USDA Geman aroma male.

hops.name: Liberty
hops.genetic_origin: A triploid seedling of the German Hallertau variety.

hops.name: Mandarina Bavaria
hops.genetic_origin: Cascade x Huell male breeding line (94/045/001 x wild PM resistant male)

hops.name: Melba
hops.aroma_spec: Passionfruit, Grapefruit, citrus and summery characteristics

hops.name: Mount Hood
hops.genetic_origin: A triploid seedling of the German Hallertauer variety; daughter of Hallertauer Mittelfrueh and sister to Liberty.

hops.name: Northern Brewer
hops.genetic_origin: A German cross between a Canterbury Golding and 'OB21' - a male seedling of Brewers Gold.

hops.name: Nugget
hops.genetic_origin: Selected from a cross between Brewers Gold and a high alpha-acid male with good storage properties; released in 1982.

hops.name: Opal
hops.genetic_origin: New variety bred in Huell

hops.name: Perle
hops.genetic_origin: A German variety bred in Huell resulting from a cross between Northern Brewer and 63/5/27M.
hops.brewhouse: Akoya, Northern Brewer, Aurora, Hallertauer Tradition

hops.name: Polaris
hops.genetic_origin: 94/075/758 x 97/060/720 (div. Huell material)

hops.name: Saazer
hops.genetic_origin: A landrace variety originating in the Czech Republic.

hops.name: Saphir
hops.genetic_origin: A cross between two new varieties 83/17/20 and 80/56/6 bred in Huell.

hops.name: Spalter
hops.genetic_origin: A landrace variety originating in Germany.
hops.aroma_spec: spicy, fruity, floral, pine, vanilla, tea

hops.name: Spalter Select
hops.genetic_origin: A cross from 76/18/80 and 71/16/7, released in 1993.

hops.name: Strisselspalter
hops.genetic_origin: Major aroma hop of the Alsace area of France.

hops.name: Styrian Golding (Celeia)
hops.genetic_origin: Styrian Golding (Celeia) is a triploid cross between Savinjski Golding and 105/58 (cross between Aurora and a Slovenian wild hop)

hops.name: Sorachi Ace
hops.genetic_origin: (Brewers's Gold x Saazer - OP) x Beikei No. 2 male - developed by Sapporo Breweries released in 1988

hops.name: Sterling
hops.genetic_origin: A diploid seedling of the Czech Saaz variety; released in 1998.

hops.name: Summit
hops.genetic_origin: Semi-dwarf super high alpha hop variety released by the American Dwarf Hop Association.

hops.name: Tahoma
hops.genetic_origin: Tahoma was released in 2013 by the USDA and Washington State University as a daughter of Glacier

hops.name: Titan
hops.genetic_origin: In 2022, a new high alpha variety was introduced by the Hop Research Center in Hüll. This variety was developed by crossing the high alpha variety Polaris and has the same crop yield as Herkules.

hops.name: Triskel
hops.genetic_origin: Triskel is a cross developped in 2006 between the French Strisselspalt variety and the male plant of the English Yeoman variety.

hops.name: Tettnanger
hops.genetic_origin: An landrace variety bred in Germany.

hops.name: Vanguard
hops.genetic_origin: A cross between a selected, Hallertauer daughter and a USDA selected, German aroma male; a triploid hop, similar to Hallertauer Mittelfrueh.

hops.name: Willamette
hops.genetic_origin: A triploid seedling of the English Fuggle variety.

hops.name: Northdown
hops.genetic_origin: Bred at Wye College from a Northern Brewer and a downy mildew-resistant male cross; closely related to both Target and Challenger; released for commercial planting in the early 1970's.

hops.name: Aurora
hops.genetic_origin: A Northern Brewer cross originating in Yugoslavia.

hops.name: Boadicea
hops.genetic_origin: Dwarf variety recently developed at Wye Hops Ltd. by Peter Darby.
hops.aroma_spec: spicy, floral, dried fruit, ripe fruit

hops.name: Progress
hops.genetic_origin: Developed at Wye College in 1951 from WGV and released in 1964 as a wilt-tolerant alternative to Fuggle.

hops.name: Bor
hops.genetic_origin: Hybrid posterity of Northern Brewer which was open pollinated by Saaz provenience components - released in the Czech Republic in 1994.

hops.name: Whitbread Golding
hops.genetic_origin: Selected as a seedling in 1911 from a little known variety called Bates' Brewer; it was eventually named after the brewery which owned the old farm.

hops.name: Santiam
hops.genetic_origin: A triploid hop resulting from a cross between 1/3 German Tettnanger, 1/3 Hallertauer Mittelfrueh and a selected tetraploid USDA male.

hops.name: Marynka
hops.genetic_origin: Polish breeding.

hops.name: Phoenix
hops.genetic_origin: Developed at Wye College; a seedling of Yeoman, this variety shows great promise as a versatile and robust new variety.

hops.name: Challenger
hops.genetic_origin: Bred at Wye College and released for commercial planting in 1972; it is a granddaughter of Northern Brewer crossed with a downy mildew resistant male and is a 'cousin' of Target.

hops.name: Sovereign
hops.genetic_origin: Dwarf variety recently developedat Wye Hops Ltd. by Peter Darby; noticeable for ist very high ratio of cones to leaf at harvest.

hops.name: First Gold
hops.genetic_origin: A dwarf hop bred at Wye College from a cross pollination of WGV with a dwarf male; released in the late nineties it has successfully progressed from trial plots into full production.

hops.name: Premiant
hops.genetic_origin: Released in the Czech Republic in 1996, descendant of the variety Northern Brewer.

hops.name: Lubelski (Lublin)
hops.genetic_origin: A landrace aroma variety thought to have been bred from a Saaz selection; grown in the area of Poland of the same name.

hops.name: Target
hops.genetic_origin: Released by Wye College in 1972 it is a 'cousin' of Challenger but with powdery mildew resistance.

hops.name: Mt. Rainier
hops.genetic_origin: Hallertauer Magnum x USDA 19085M - cross made in 1994 in Corvallis OR and released in 2009

hops.name: Motueka
hops.genetic_origin: Released in 1998 from Hort Research, bred from a cross between Saaz and a NZ breeding selection. Initially called Belgian Saaz, now abbreviated to 'B' Saaz
hops.aroma_spec: Fresh lime, lemon zest, mojito, citrus

hops.name: Nelson Sauvin
hops.genetic_origin: A triploid variety developed at Hort Research, Riwaka Research Centre from a Smoothcone and NZ male cross; first released in 2000.

hops.name: Smaragd
hops.genetic_origin: New variety bred in Huell

hops.name: Admiral
hops.genetic_origin: Bred at Wye College to complement Target. Released in the late nineties and still growing in acreage, it promises eventually to yield higher than Target.

hops.name: Bobek
hops.genetic_origin: A cross between Northern Brewer and a wild hop.

hops.name: Pilgrim
hops.genetic_origin: A new variety registered by Wye College in 2001.

hops.name: Pride of Ringwood
hops.genetic_origin: Bred in Australia from an English variety - Pride of Kent; released in 1965.

hops.name: Sládek
hops.genetic_origin: Hybrid posterity of Northern Brewer, Osvald's close No. 126 and male components from Czech provenience - released in the Czech Republic in 1994.

hops.name: Bramling Cross
hops.genetic_origin: Bred at Wye in the 1920's from a Bramling (a traditional Golding variety) and a male seedling of the Manitoban wild hop.
